A type of tree with a few rules

Binary tree:
Each node can have either zero, one or two nodes and each child can only have one parent

Level 0: 2^0 = 1 (1 node)
Level 1: 2^1 = 2 (2 nodes)
Level 2: 2^2 = 4 (4 nodes)
Level 3: 2^3 = 8 (8 nodes)

number of nodes = 2^h (height) -1; --> O numero de nodes total contando os nodes acima e no mesmo nível
log nodes = height

log 100 = 2 (because 10^2 = 100)


